.TH "DALMA\-SLURM_ENVIRONMENT" "" "June 2016" "NYUAD" "Dalma Manual"
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
Here is the list of some of the environment variables set by SLURM when a job starts in the master node
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBSLURM_JOB_ID\fR: The ID of the job
.
.P
\fBSLURM_JOB_NAME\fR: Name of the job
.
.P
\fBSLURM_JOB_NODELIST\fR: List of nodes allocated to the job
.
.P
\fBSLURM_JOB_NUM_NODES\fR: Total number of nodes in the job\'s resource allocation
.
.P
\fBSLURM_JOB_CPUS_PER_NODE\fR: Count of processors available to the job on this node
.
.P
\fBSLURM_PROCID\fR: The MPI rank (or relative process ID) of the current process
.
.P
\fBSLURM_ARRAY_JOB_ID\fR: Job array\'s master job ID number
.
.P
\fBSLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID\fR: Job array ID (index) number
.
.P
\fBSLURM_ARRAY_TASK_MAX\fR: Job array\'s maximum ID (index) number
.
.P
\fBSLURM_ARRAY_TASK_MIN\fR: Job array\'s minimum ID (index) number
.
.P
\fBSLURM_NTASKS\fR: Number of tasks in the job
.
.P
\fBSLURM_TASKS_PER_NODE\fR: Number of tasks to be initiated on each node, comma separated list
.
.P
\fBSLURM_CPUS_ON_NODE\fR: Number of CPUS on the allocated node
.
.P
\fBSLURM_CPUS_PER_TASK\fR: Number of cpus requested per task
.
.P
\fBSLURM_STEP_ID\fR: The step ID of the current job (srun)
.
.P
\fBSLURM_TASK_PID\fR: The process ID of the task being started
.
.P
\fBSLURM_NODEID\fR: The relative node ID of the current node
.
